An international management practitioner, Professor Adetunji  Haastrup has won the Annual Global Leadership Award for  2021, organised by Global Corporation, Mogul Inc. New York, USA. The awardees consist of 100 winners from the major five continents of the world (Europe, Americas, Asia, Africa and Australia). Interestingly, Haastrup was the only winner from the African continent. Haastrup holds milestone records. He is Nigeria’s first professor of Human Services Management, first African to become an Ambassador of Management, first Nigerian to become fellow in management from the International Academy of Management simultaneously from Nigeria and UK and also the first Nigerian to become a member of the European Commission’s Network, Brussels, Belgium.   North must produce Buhari’s successor, says Bala…     Amid probe, Abba Kyari makes first public appearance at IGP…     APC chair: Governors in the dark as Buhari keeps party…   - Advertisement - He was recently appointed as a council member of the Harvard Business Review, Cambridge, USA. He is also a member of Harvard University, Boston Massachusetts, USA and the United Nations Foundation, Washington USA. Prof Haastrup made history in 2004 when he was selected From Africa  to the UN Roundtable Talk on education. The Forum included former Education Minister, Prof Babs Fafunwa and former UNIBEN Vice Chancellor, Prof. Alele Williams. The British Council honoured him with a special invitation to be a part of the inaugural British Council Management Forum in Nov 2005. He is presently a Faculty Advisor to Advancing Canadian Entrepreneurship, Ontario Canada and Professor of Management (MBA Class) At Caleb University, Lagos Nigeria.